{"title": "Red Flower", "description": "LibriVox volunteers bring you 27 recordings of The Red Flower by Henry van Dyke. This was the Weekly Poetry project for March 11, 2012.<br><br>Dr. Henry van Dyke was an American author, lecturer, ambassador and pastor. He was in charge of the committee which wrote The Book of Common Worship of 1906, the first printed Presbyterian liturgy.<br>He wrote many poems, short stories, hymns and essays, often with religious themes.<br>This particular poem, written after the outbreak of World War I but set beforehand, contrasts the natural beauty of the summer before the war with the horror and destruction that is to follow. (Summary by Lucy Perry)", "duration": 3320, "language": "English", "authors": [{"id": "836", "name": "Henry van Dyke"}], "coverArt": "http://archive.org/download/LibrivoxCdCoverArt22/Red_Flower_1209.jpg", "copyright_year": "0", "genres": ["Poetry", "Multi-version (Weekly and Fortnightly poetry)"], "supporters": [{"role": "Read by", "name": "LibriVox Volunteers"}, {"role": "Book Coordinator", "name": "Lucy Perry"}, {"role": "Meta Coordinator", "name": "David Lawrence"}], "sections": [{"section": 1, "title": "The Red Flower - Read by CC", "readers": [4586], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1203_librivox/redflower_vandyke_cc_64kb.mp3", "duration": 128}, {"section": 2, "title": "The Red Flower - Read by DVB", "readers": [7243], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1203_librivox/redflower_vandyke_dvb_64kb.mp3", "duration": 110}, {"section": 3, "title": "The Red Flower - Read by EEP", "readers": [2825], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1203_librivox/redflower_vandyke_eep_64kb.mp3", "duration": 136}, {"section": 4, "title": "The Red Flower - Read by FS", "readers": [6735], "path": "http://www.archive.org/download/red_flower_1203_librivox/redflower_vandyke_fs_64kb.mp3", "duration": 118}, {"section": 5, "title": "The Red Flower - Read by GC", "readers": [6733], "path": "ht